cutoff_energies = [4.0, 95] # Varied cutoff energies within plausible range

        material = random.choice(target_materials) # Randomly choose a target material from the list

        intensity = round(random.uniform(*intensities), 16) # Acknowledging the high variance in intensity, rounded to a manageable number

        cutoff_energy = random.uniform(*cutoff_energies)
        
        # Simplified relationships (for illustration; not strictly based on provided statistics)

            intensity += random.uniform(1e18, 6e20) # Intensity slightly varies for "plastic" as an example simplification

    return samples
